# Cursor Rules — SMAUII Core (Backend Laravel)

## Project Context
- Stack: Laravel 13, PHP 8.4, PostgreSQL 16 (NeonDB), Sanctum
- Architecture: Monorepo submodule core.git
- Frontend: InertiaJS 3 + React 19 + TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, Vite 8

## Code Style
- PHP: PSR-12 (Laravel Pint)
- TypeScript/React: ESLint + Prettier
- Follow Laravel conventions strictly
- Use Eloquent ORM for all database queries
- No raw SQL unless absolutely necessary

## AI Behavior
- Laravel best practices: Form Request for validation, Policy for authorization, Eloquent for queries
- Inertia best practices: use Inertia::render for pages, share data via middleware, use React components for UI
- Security: validate inputs, escape outputs, use CSRF
- Performance: eager loading (with()), no N+1, index database columns
- Testing: PHPUnit for backend, Vitest/React Testing Library for frontend

## Conventions
- Routes: web.php for Inertia pages, api.php for Sanctum API
- Controllers: __invoke for single action, resource controller for CRUD
- Pages: resources/js/Pages/*.tsx — one file per route
- Components: resources/js/Components/*.tsx — reusable UI
- Layouts: resources/js/Layouts/*.tsx — page layouts
- Types: resources/js/types/*.ts — TypeScript definitions
- Database: migrations up/down, seeders with factories
- Validation: Form Request classes with authorize() method
- Authorization: Laravel Policies, not Gates

## Important Rules
- Never commit .env, keys, tokens, or passwords
- Never use dd() or var_dump() in committed code
- Never skip validation — always validate user input
- Never query inside loops (N+1!)
- Use TypeScript for all frontend code (.tsx/.ts)
- Use bun instead of npm for package management

## Commands
- php artisan test — PHPUnit tests
- ./vendor/bin/pint — Laravel Pint (code style check)
- bun run build — Build frontend assets
- bun run dev — Start Vite dev server
- php artisan migrate — Run migrations
- php artisan migrate:fresh --seed — Reset + seed database

## References
- ../aksesekolah/docs/* — Documentation
- ../smauii-playbook/* — SOPs, workflows, templates
